        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Exodus 35</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l><emph>Parashat Vayakhel</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="1">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            Moses gathered all the congregation of the children
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            of Israel together, and said to them, ‘These are the words
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            which the Lord commanded, that you should do them.</l>
                        <l n="2">Six days
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            work shall be done, but on the seventh day you shall have
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            Sabbath, a day of complete rest holy to the Lord. Everyone who does work
                            on it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            shall be put to death.</l>
                        <l n="3">You shall kindle no fire in all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            your dwelling places on the Sabbath day.’</l>
                        <l n="4">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            And Moses spoke to all the congregation of the children of Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            saying, ‘This is the word which the Lord has commanded, saying,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                        <l n="5">“Take from among you an heave offering to the Lord. Everyone who
                            has a generous
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            heart shall bring the heave offering of the Lord: gold, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            silver, and bronze,</l>
                        <l n="6">And blue and purple and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            scarlet silk, and linen, and goats’ hair,</l>
                        <l n="7">
                            <milestone unit="page" n="146v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            And rams’ skins dyed red, and porpoise skins,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            and acacia wood,</l>
                        <l n="8">And oil for the light, and spices
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            for anointing oil and for the sweet incense.</l>
                        <l n="9">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            And onyx stones for the ephod, and stones to be set for the
                            breastplate.</l>
                        <l n="10">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            And every wise hearted among you shall come and make all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            that the Lord has commanded Moses.</l>
                        <l n="11">The tabernacle,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            and its tent, and its covering, its hooks,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            and its boards, and its bars,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            its pillars, and its bases,</l>
                        <l n="12">The
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            ark, and its poles, the cover |of the ark|, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            veil of the covering,</l>
                        <l n="13">The table, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            its poles, and all its equipment, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            showbread,</l>
                        <l n="14">And the lampstand for the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            light, and its equipment, and its places for candles,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            and the oil for the light,</l>
                        <l n="15">And the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            incense altar, and its poles, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            anointing oil, and the incense of sweet spices, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            the cover for the door, for the door of the tabernacle,</l>
                        <l n="16">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            The altar of burnt offering, and the bronze grate of it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            its poles, and all its equipment, the basin
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            and its place,</l>
                        <l n="17">The curtains
                            <milestone unit="page" n="147r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            of the court, its pillars, and their bases, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            cover for the gate of the court,</l>
                        <l n="18">The pegs of the tabernacle,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            and the pegs of the court, and their cords,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="19">The colourful garments to do service in the Holy,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            the holy garments for Aaron, the priest, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            garments of his sons, for their service as priests.”’</l>
                        <l n="20">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            all the congregation of the children of Israel departed from before
                            Moses.</l>
                        <l n="21">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            And they came, everyone whose heart guided him and everyone
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            whom his spirit made generous brought the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            Lord’s heave offering for the work of the tent of meeting, and for all
                            its service,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            and for the holy garments.</l>
                        <l n="22">And they came,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            men and women. And all the generous hearted brought
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            bracelets, and earrings, and rings, and trinkets, every |kind of| gold
                            item: and every
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            man who gave a wave offering of gold to the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="23">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            every man with whom was found blue and purple and scarlet silk,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            and linen, and goats’ hair, and rams’ skins dyed red,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            and porpoise skins: they brought |them|.</l>
                        <l n="24">Everyone
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            who donated an heave offering of silver and bronze brought the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            Lord’s heave offering. And every man with whom was found acacia
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            wood for any work of the service: they brought |it|.</l>
                        <l n="25">And all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            the women who were wise hearted spun with their hands and brought
                            <milestone unit="page" n="147v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            <supplied reason="lost">yarn</supplied>, the blue, and the purple, and
                            the scarlet
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            silk, and the linen.</l>
                        <l n="26">And all the women whose
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            heart guided them in wisdom spun
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            goats’ hair.</l>
                        <l n="27">And the princes brought
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            onyx stones, and stones for the ephod, and stones to be set
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            for the breastplate,</l>
                        <l n="28">And the spice, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            oil for the light and for the anointing oil and for the sweet
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            incense.</l>
                        <l n="29">Every men and women whose heart made them generous
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            to bring for all the work that the Lord had commanded
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            to do by the prophecy of Moses: the children of Israel brought
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            a freewill offering to the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="30">And Moses said to the children
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            of Israel, ‘See, the Lord has called by name Bezalel, son of Uri,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah.</l>
                        <l n="31">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            he has filled him with the spirit of God, with wisdom, with
                            understanding, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            with knowledge in every |kind| of work,</l>
                        <l n="32">And to make patterns,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            to work in gold and in silver and in bronze,</l>
                        <l n="33">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            And to fill with a mason, and to do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            all kind of patterned work with a woodworker.</l>
                        <l n="34">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            he put teaching in his heart: he and Oholiab, son of Ahisamach,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            of the tribe of Dan.</l>
                        <l n="35">He has filled them with wisdom of heart,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            to do all the work of master |workmen|, and of the embroiderer, and of needlework
                            <milestone unit="page" n="148r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            in blue and in purple in scarlet silk and in linen, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            of the weaver: of those who do any work, and of those that make all
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Ex035-P148r-L3_trl" n="3" next="ADub.III.73.002.036.trl.xml#Ex036-P148r-L3_trl" />
                            |kind of| patterns.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
